{"id": 225032304, "title": "Action! Windsor's first International Black Film Festival opens this summer", "text": "The Windsor International Black Film Festival runs August 16 to 18. The first day will include a meet-and-greet mixer. Day two will offer a table discussion and daylong screenings. The highlight of day three will be a red-carpet awards ceremony.", "summary": "They might be heroes and they could be villains, but one thing is for sure \u2014 they won\u2019t die first.\u00a0 The curtain will rise this summer for the premiere of\u00a0the Windsor International Black Film Festival, a three-day event highlighting artists and stories that are often undervalued and overlooked.\u00a0 \u201cI always joke, when I watch films [&#8230;]", "url": "https://windsorstar.com/news/local-news/action-windsors-first-international-black-film-festival-opens-this-summer", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/windsorstar/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/film.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:13:12", "author": "Trevor Wilhelm", "authors": ["Trevor Wilhelm"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": 0.606}